results.name: Aquathereum
results.description: Aquathereum - blockchain integrated  MMO game
results.fullDescription:
Aquathereum is an unscripted blockchain integrated Massively Multiplayer Online (MMO) game where the economy is run by the players and is driven by in game mining, combat, exploration, trading, manufacturing, and quests. Ships, modules, and other in game assets are ERC-721 tokens on the Ethereum blockchain which are owned, traded, and sold by the players. 

Aquathereum takes place more than 200 years in the future on the planet Exus, over 30 lightyears away from earth. Exus was a colony of planet Earth, but due to the distance and difficulty in managing the decentralized government, Earth’s reigning government gave independence to Exus. The game is based in an underwater world where players quest, mine, craft, war, and build powerful allies and clans in an effort to gain control and power, wage war on their enemies, and build the most magnificent underwater bases, buildings, ships, and modules Exus has ever seen. Assets in Aquathereum are player owned on the blockchain – players have full control of their assets and can sell and trade them as they wish outside of the game (in game marketplace will be available as well). The planet is primarily covered by water, however, resource rich pockets of land exist throughout the world and can be found, colonized, and fought over for the resources, ships, buildings, and structures (surface and land based play is a future phase of development).

results.name: Ticketh
results.description: Simple ethereum lottery.
results.fullDescription:
Rules:
- Every player can buy more than one ticket. (buy more tickets if you are not the only player)
- Every player can participate in more than one lottery.
- Lottery starts when first ticket is bought for the round.
- The lottery duration is current block number when starting + duration blocks.
- Once the current block number reaches the lottery block number only one more ticket can be submitted.
- When the last ticket is submitted the lottery ends and a winner is selected.
- Winner is determined by a random number and prize is received within seconds.
- Prize is calculated when there is more than one participant. 10% tax is for the lottery owner.
- Displayed prize includes the last entry.

Randomness:
Unpredictable randomness is achieved by using the Chainlink decentralized oracles.

results.name: 0xRacing
results.description: Tokenized eSports / racing racecar sponsorships
results.fullDescription:
0xRacing is at the intersection of eSports, sim racing, and motorsports. 0xRacing is building an eSports sim racing team organized on the Ethereum Blockchain via DAO structure.

https://0xracing.github.io
https://github.com/0xRacing/Whitepaper

While we have a larger vision and roadmap we are building towards, a core focus at the start is tokenization of sponsorship opportunities within eSports / sim racing. Current eSport opportunities rely on content creator videos / streams to spread brand awareness. With global online sim racing, a brand can spread awareness directly on a racecar just like their real life counterparts. This helps bring exposure to not only viewers of videos / streams, but directly reaches players around the world in-game. Quite often you can be found racing against some of the most elite professional drivers in the world. The likes of Lando Norris and Max Verstappen (Formula 1) and Dale Earnhardt Jr (Former NASCAR) can be found nearly daily racing in various series on iRacing. 

0xRacing has just launched the dynamic ERC-721 token, 0xR. This token captures sponsorship opportunities across the team, and then converts to a Proof of Sponsorship token at the completion of the sponsorship period. Our initial tokens have just been listed on OpenSea in DAI!
